Package: snownews
Version: 1.5.4
Revision: 1
Description: Text mode RSS/RDF newsreader
License: GPL
Maintainer: Khairulmizam Samsudin <xource@users.sourceforge.net>

# Dependencies
Depends: ncurses-shlibs, libxml2-shlibs, gettext, libiconv
BuildDepends: ncurses-dev, libxml2, gettext-dev, libiconv-dev

# Unpack Phase
Source: http://kiza.kcore.de/software/snownews/download/snownews-%v.tar.gz
SourceDirectory: snownews-%v
Source-MD5: 1165207017bbda339b6091946289b984  

# Patch Phase
PatchScript: sed 's|FINK_PREFIX|%i|g' < %a/%n.patch | patch -p1

# Compile Phase 
CompileScript: <<
make
<<
GCC: 3.3

# Install Phase
DocFiles: AUTHOR COPYING CREDITS Changelog README README.colors README.patching 
InstallScript: <<
make install prefix=%i

mkdir -p %i/share/doc/%n/examples
install -m 644 opml2snow %i/share/doc/%n/examples
<<

# Additional Data
Homepage: http://kiza.kcore.de/software/snownews/index.en
DescDetail: <<
  Snownews is a text mode RSS/RDF newsreader. It supports all versions of RSS 
  natively and supports other formats via plugins.

  Features
  * Fast and very resource friendly.
  * Builtin HTTP client will follow server redirects
  * Handles gzip compression.
  * Local cache for minimal network traffic.
  * HTTP proxy support.
  * Color support.
  * Extensible via plugins.
  * Feed categories and many other useful features!
<<
DescUsage: <<
  Refer to snownews(1) man pages for usage and see README.colors for 
  color support in snownews.  
<<
DescPort: <<
-Configuration does not use autotools. Patch to use variable FINK_PREFIX
-opml2snow moved to doc/examples, because it require XML::LibXML or fink libxml-pm installed
<<
